unknown Quiet Riot.

01:25:09.521 --> 01:25:12.273
It wasn't even really
a leap of faith because,

01:25:12.274 --> 01:25:14.402
I mean, I have
faith in Quiet Riot,

01:25:14.403 --> 01:25:17.405
that we could sell
maybe 50,000 records a year

01:25:17.406 --> 01:25:19.623
and make a living, play, you
know...

01:25:19.624 --> 01:25:23.242
We didn't aspire
for anything bigger than that.

01:25:23.243 --> 01:25:25.041
We just wanted
to make another record.

01:25:26.204 --> 01:25:29.999
So, we have Metal Health
finished.

01:25:30.000 --> 01:25:31.092
Ready to be released.

01:25:32.169 --> 01:25:33.762
And we couldn't find a manager.

01:25:35.797 --> 01:25:37.673
We would say,
"Listen to this record."

01:25:37.674 --> 01:25:39.345
"Eh, I don't know,
that kind of music

01:25:39.346 --> 01:25:42.096
I don't think is really ever
gonna come back."

01:25:42.097 --> 01:25:46.724
So, our beginning with Quiet Riot
was very, very humble beginnings.

01:25:46.725 --> 01:25:49.604
We were driving ourselves
in a station wagon,

01:25:49.605 --> 01:25:52.647
playing up and down
the pacific coast.

01:25:52.648 --> 01:25:54.982
And by the time the tour ended,

01:25:54.983 --> 01:25:57.780
we were in Denver
and the promoter Barry Faith,

01:25:57.781 --> 01:26:01.157
