I could set my watch.

01:26:58.465 --> 01:27:01.137
Because every half hour
Come On Feel The Noise came on

01:27:01.138 --> 01:27:03.634
on MTV, you know,
Music Television.

01:27:03.635 --> 01:27:04.635
Who knew?

01:27:04.636 --> 01:27:05.979
And by November,

01:27:07.180 --> 01:27:09.014
we had a number one album.

01:27:09.015 --> 01:27:12.986
We're talking number one when
your competition is Thriller,

01:27:12.987 --> 01:27:15.312
Synchronicity by the Police,

01:27:15.313 --> 01:27:17.565
and all those those
incredible albums.

01:27:17.566 --> 01:27:20.109
So, to me it wasn't just about,

01:27:20.110 --> 01:27:21.487
having a number one album...

01:27:21.488 --> 01:27:23.284
It was about being in such

01:27:24.281 --> 01:27:26.198
great company.

01:27:26.199 --> 01:27:30.035
What's really interesting
about going to the top,

01:27:30.036 --> 01:27:32.329
with any group is that,

01:27:32.330 --> 01:27:35.499
your landscape
is exactly the same,

01:27:35.500 --> 01:27:38.595
because I've experienced that
with three bands.

01:27:38.596 --> 01:27:40.385
Going from the bottom,

01:27:41.006 --> 01:27:42.590
to the very top.

01:27:42.591 --> 01:27:44.592
I did it with Ozzy,

01:27:44.593 --> 01:27:47.688
I experienced that with Quiet Riot,
and then later on with Whitesnake.

01:27:47.689 --> 01:27:49.597
And then once you get there,

01:27:49.598 --> 01:27:52.433
the trick is to stay there.
[laughs]

01:27:52.434 --> 01:27:53.976
To stay on the top,

01:27:53.977 --> 01:27:56.228
which is because there's
plenty of room at the bottom.

01:27:56.229 --> 01:27:57.697
There's only so much
room at the top.

01:27:57.698 --> 01:27:59.985
There's only gonna be people
trying to push you,

01:27:59.986 --> 01:28:01.822
you know, shove you
off the the top.

01:28:01.823 --> 01:28:04.287
So, that is the toughest thing
to accomplish.

01:28:04.288 --> 01:28:06.197
Getting to the top is hard.

01:28:06.198 --> 01:28:08.576
Staying at the top
is virtually impossible.

01:28:10.160 --> 01:28:12.254
I wish I would have
the foresight,

01:28:12.255 --> 01:28:15.122
to predict any of the band's
successes,

01:28:15.123 --> 01:28:17.087
or you would just have
to follow your heart.

01:28:17.088 --> 01:28:20.461
And after doing this for a while
I began to see the signs.

01:28:20.462 --> 01:28:22.508
You know, I began
to realize that,

01:28:22.509 --> 01:28:24.507
all of these
opportunities, to be...

01:28:24.508 --> 01:28:26.761
To be playing with some
of the greatest musicians,

01:28:27.511 --> 01:28:28.552
in the world,

01:28:28.553 --> 01:28:29.804
actually are...

01:28:29.805 --> 01:28:31.557
It's a blessing to do that.

01:28:32.349 --> 01:28:34.141
The Ozzy Band.

01:28:34.142 --> 01:28:37.567
I played with Quiet Riot and
achieved such incredible heights,

01:28:37.568 --> 01:28:39.355
you know, success.

01:28:39.356 --> 01:28:41.649
To go on stage with Whitesnake,

01:28:41.650 --> 01:28:43.776
a band that I'd been a fan of.

01:28:43.777 --> 01:28:45.277
My God!

01:28:45.278 --> 01:28:48.202
So, it took me a few years
to actually have the time,

01:28:48.203 --> 01:28:50.825
to look back and really relish,

01:28:50.826 --> 01:28:53.830
in all of the success
that I've been blessed with.

01:28:53.831 --> 01:28:56.747
And after all said and clone,

01:28:56.748 --> 01:29:00.093
the most important thing
that you have to remember,

01:29:01.086 --> 01:29:03.087
is the journey itself.

01:29:03.088 --> 01:29:04.797
That's when you say,

01:29:04.798 --> 01:29:06.549
"Oh, wow, check this out.

01:29:06.550 --> 01:29:08.092
I've accomplished this."

01:29:08.093 --> 01:29:09.470
But I've gotta tell you,

01:29:09.471 --> 01:29:10.928
it's the people,

01:29:10.929 --> 01:29:13.848
that I am on the journey
along with.

01:29:13.849 --> 01:29:15.683
That is priceless!

01:29:15.684 --> 01:29:16.892
That really is.

01:29:16.893 --> 01:29:18.019
And that is...

01:29:18.937 --> 01:29:21.315
why I get out of bed everyday.

01:29:22.399 --> 01:29:24.441
Since I made God a promise

01:29:24.442 --> 01:29:28.571
that as long as my fingers were gonna
keep moving I was gonna keep playing.

01:29:28.572 --> 01:29:30.666
I can't go back on my
promise, you know.

01:29:30.667 --> 01:29:33.284
This is what I do.
Lam a musician.

01:29:33.285 --> 01:29:34.286
I must play.

01:29:38.999 --> 01:29:43.095
[man] I'd like to introduce
you to, Liberty DeVitto!

01:29:51.011 --> 01:29:52.261
How's it going?

01:29:52.262 --> 01:29:53.512
[all] Good!

01:29:53.513 --> 01:29:55.982
One of the last things
that was ever said to me

01:29:55.983 --> 01:29:58.517
while I was on the road
with Billy,

01:29:58.518 --> 01:30:00.477
came from the piano tuner.

01:30:00.478 --> 01:30:01.854
We were walking
down the street

01:30:01.855 --> 01:30:04.151
I remember coming
from breakfast or something.

01:30:04.152 --> 01:30:06.070
We weren't even talking,
just silent,

01:30:06.071 --> 01:30:07.613
He just turned to me
and he goes,

01:30:07.614 --> 01:30:09.325
"You know what your problem is?

01:30:09.326 --> 01:30:10.493
You're a nice guy."

01:30:18.788 --> 01:30:22.333
You're the drums.
The center of everything.

01:30:22.334 --> 01:30:24.462
Like almost being
the center of the universe.

01:30:24.463 --> 01:30:28.803
We're the ones that make people get
up when they dance. It's our beat.

01:30:28.804 --> 01:30:33.429
So' Little Kids Rock puts instruments
and gives free lessons to kids,

01:30:33.430 --> 01:30:36.523
where their school program has
been taken out of the school

01:30:36.524 --> 01:30:39.975
in underprivileged schools,
like in Harlem...

01:30:39.976 --> 01:30:42.980
and you know, down and out
areas in different cities.

01:30:42.981 --> 01:30:45.481
Little Kids Rock has been
a saving grace for me.

01:30:45.482 --> 01:30:46.654
That was fun, right?

01:30:46.655 --> 01:30:47.858
[all] Yeah!

01:30:47.859 --> 01:30:49.735
Music is always fun.
It's a lot of fun.

01:30:49.736 --> 01:30:52.157
It's a great way to burn off
energy and stuff like that.

01:30:52.158 --> 01:30:56.205
And, you know whats great about it
is going from emotion to emotion.

01:30:56.206 --> 01:30:58.869
Like a fast song
to a slow song.

01:30:58.870 --> 01:31:00.412
Reflecting back,

01:31:00.413 --> 01:31:01.835
we made great records.

01:31:01.836 --> 01:31:02.957
We really did.

01:31:02.958 --> 01:31:05.552
I mean, those records
will last forever.

01:31:05.553 --> 01:31:08.128
People still get off
on that stuff.

01:31:08.129 --> 01:31:10.844
Every time I'm driving in the
car and the station plays,

01:31:10.845 --> 01:31:14.306
Scenes from an Italian Restaurant,
like, "Yeah, that's me playing."

01:31:14.307 --> 01:31:17.181
You know, and when
I hear that stuff, people say,

01:31:17.182 --> 01:31:18.722
"Does it upset you?"

01:31:18.723 --> 01:31:21.520
And I say, "No, I just go
right back to the studio,

01:31:21.521 --> 01:31:24.567
and what it was like in the
studio making that record."

01:31:24.568 --> 01:31:26.522
We were like brothers.

01:31:26.523 --> 01:31:29.618
It was like going to war and we've
got very successful at what we did.

01:31:30.652 --> 01:31:33.195
If Billy is the father,

01:31:33.196 --> 01:31:34.743
the parent of those songs,

01:31:34.744 --> 01:31:37.074
I'm at least the uncle,
you know.

01:31:37.075 --> 01:31:39.749
But now if I saw Billy I'd hug
him and tell him I love him.

01:31:39.750 --> 01:31:42.705
If he called me up and said,

01:31:42.706 --> 01:31:44.879
"I'm sorry. Do you
want to play again?"

01:31:45.875 --> 01:31:47.418
I'd Say, "Yeah"

01:31:47.419 --> 01:31:50.587
Playing music gives
you an identity.

01:31:50.588 --> 01:31:53.799
It really, like,
"look what I can do!

01:31:53.800 --> 01:31:56.140
It took me a long time
to learn how to do this.

01:31:56.141 --> 01:31:57.932
But look what I can do now."

01:31:57.933 --> 01:32:01.559
So, it's a great, great thing to
learn how to play an instrument.

01:32:01.560 --> 01:32:03.058
And it's not too bad.

01:32:03.059 --> 01:32:05.312
I got my shot. My mother
used to tell me all the time,

01:32:05.313 --> 01:32:08.155
"Lib, you had your turn.
Now it's the young guys turns."

01:32:09.232 --> 01:32:10.946
But right now life is good.

01:32:10.947 --> 01:32:13.161
I play all the time,
great people.

01:32:13.162 --> 01:32:14.236
You know.

01:32:14.237 --> 01:32:15.363
It's cool.

01:32:34.632 --> 01:32:37.848
I want to see Bucket-head
get together with the other guy

01:32:37.849 --> 01:32:39.139
